<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
  OWASP Dependency-Check suppression file (the chapter's false-positive / "vulnerable != exploitable"
  discipline, Chapter 19's reviewed-suppression rule applied to SCA). A suppression here removes a finding
  from the gate; the rule is that every entry records WHY, reviewed, with a date — never a silent or
  blanket suppression. CPE-based matching is fuzzy and will flag CVEs that do not apply; the answer is a
  reviewed suppression with a justification, not turning the gate off.

  This file is consumed by the -Pscan profile (dependency-check-maven 12.2.2, SOURCE-PIN §4). The schema
  is the published OWASP DC suppression schema (dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd). The single entry below
  shows the SHAPE of a reviewed suppression; it is scoped narrowly to one coordinate AND to one named
  finding, so it is inert unless a scan produces exactly that finding and cannot mask anything else.

  The finding identifier below is a documented PLACEHOLDER (vulnerabilityName "ILLUSTRATIVE-FP-PLACEHOLDER"),
  not a real CVE. A real suppression names the actual reviewed CVE here; we do not invent a CVE number,
  because a CVE id is a fact that must trace to NVD (SOURCE-PIN never-invent). Using a clearly-labelled
  vulnerabilityName keeps the discipline visible without asserting a vulnerability that does not exist.
-->
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">
  <!-- tag::depcheck-suppression[] -->
  <suppress>
    <notes><![CDATA[
      Reviewed false positive (2026-06-26, on-call + security review). Fuzzy CPE matching flagged a
      finding whose affected code path is not present in this artifact, so it is not exploitable here.
      Scoped to one coordinate AND one named finding, not a blanket rule. Re-review on the next bump.
    ]]></notes>
    <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/org\.apache\.commons/commons-lang3@.*$</packageUrl>
    <vulnerabilityName>ILLUSTRATIVE-FP-PLACEHOLDER</vulnerabilityName>
  </suppress>
  <!-- end::depcheck-suppression[] -->
</suppressions>
